      • createGroup

        @Transactional(rollbackFor={org.springframework.security.acls.model.AlreadyExistsException.class,org.springframework.security.acls.model.NotFoundException.class,org.springframework.dao.DataIntegrityViolationException.class})
public Group createGroup(GroupParameters groupParameters)
        Description copied from interface: GroupService
        Given a GroupParameters object, create a group and save it in the data store. If groupParameters contains a name and a null parent id, then a root type group is created. If groupParameters has both a name and a parent group id then an intermediate type group is created. If the parent group id given is not in the data store then a root group type is created.
        Specified by:
        createGroup in interface GroupService
        Returns:
        The Group that was created
        See Also:
        net.sf.sail.webapp.service.group.GroupService#createGroup(net.sf.sail.webapp.domain.group.impl.GroupParameters)
